.SH "NAME"
groupmod \- modify a crew definizzle on tha system
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'\fBgroupmod\fR\ 'u
\fBgroupmod\fR [\fIoptions\fR] \fIGROUP\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
The
\fBgroupmod\fR
command modifies tha definizzle of tha specified
\fIGROUP\fR
by modifyin tha appropriate entry up in tha crew database\&.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.PP
Da options which apply ta the
\fBgroupmod\fR
command are:
.PP
\fB\-g\fR, \fB\-\-gid\fR \fIGID\fR
.RS 4
Da crew ID of tha given
\fIGROUP\fR
will be chizzled to
\fIGID\fR\&.
.sp
Da value of
\fIGID\fR
must be a non\-negatizzle decimal integer\&. This value must be unique, unless the
\fB\-o\fR
option is used\&.
.sp
Users whoz ass use tha crew as primary crew is ghon be updated ta keep tha crew as they primary group\&.
.sp
Any filez dat have tha oldschool crew ID n' must continue ta belong to
\fIGROUP\fR, must have they crew ID chizzled manually\&.
.sp
No checks is ghon be performed wit regard ta the
\fBGID_MIN\fR,
\fBGID_MAX\fR,
\fBSYS_GID_MIN\fR, or
\fBSYS_GID_MAX\fR
from
/etc/login\&.defs\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
.RS 4
Display help message n' exit\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-new\-name\fR \fINEW_GROUP\fR
.RS 4
Da name of tha crew is ghon be chizzled from
\fIGROUP\fR
to
\fINEW_GROUP\fR
name\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-non\-unique\fR
.RS 4
When used wit the
\fB\-g\fR
option, allow ta chizzle tha group
\fIGID\fR
to a non\-unique value\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-password\fR \fIPASSWORD\fR
.RS 4
Da encrypted password, as returned by
\fBcrypt\fR(3)\&.
.sp

\fBNote:\fR
This option aint recommended cuz tha password (or encrypted password) is ghon be visible by playas listin tha processes\&.
.sp
Yo ass should make shizzle tha password respects tha system\*(Aqs password policy\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB\-R\fR, \fB\-\-root\fR \fICHROOT_DIR\fR
.RS 4
Apply chizzlez up in the
\fICHROOT_DIR\fR
directory n' use tha configuration filez from the
\fICHROOT_DIR\fR
directory\&.
.RE
.SH "CONFIGURATION"
.PP
Da followin configuration variablez in
/etc/login\&.defs
change tha behavior of dis tool:
.PP
\fBMAX_MEMBERS_PER_GROUP\fR (number)
.RS 4
Maximum thugz per crew entry\&. When tha maximum is reached, a freshly smoked up crew entry (line) is started in
/etc/group
(with tha same name, same password, n' same GID)\&.
.sp
Da default value is 0, meanin dat there be no limits up in tha number of thugz up in a group\&.
.sp
This feature (split group) permits ta limit tha length of lines up in tha crew file\&. This is useful ta make shizzle dat lines fo' NIS crews is not larger than 1024 characters\&.
.sp
If you need ta enforce such limit, you can use 25\&.
.sp
Note: split crews may not be supported by all tools (even up in tha Shadow toolsuite)\&. Yo ass should not use dis variable unless you straight-up need it\&.
.RE
